''[[Mystery Science Theater 3000]]'' (''MST3K'') <!--DO NOT CHANGE-->is<!--to was. A television show will always exist, even if production of episodes stop.--> an American television comedy series created by [[Joel Hodgson]] and originally produced by [[Best Brains|Best Brains, Inc.]] The show premiered on [[WUCW|KTMA]] (now WUCW) in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]], on November 24, 1988. The next year, in 1989, the show began its national run on [[The Comedy Channel (American TV channel)|The Comedy Channel]], running for two seasons. It continued for five more seasons on [[Comedy Central]] following The Comedy Channel's merger with [[Ha! (TV channel)|Ha!: TV Comedy Network]]. It was cancelled in 1996, but the following year was picked up by [[Syfy|The Sci-Fi Channel]] and aired for three more seasons there until another cancellation in August 1999 (although repeats continued until 2004). A sixty-episode [[Broadcast syndication|syndication]] package titled ''The Mystery Science Theater Hour'' was produced in 1995.<ref>[http://www.tv.com/shows/the-mystery-science-theater-hour/ The Mystery Science Theater Hour-TV.com]</ref>

In 2015, Hodgson led a [[crowdfunding|crowdfunded]] revival of the series with 14 episodes in its eleventh season which was released on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/US/2017/02/22/Mystery-Science-Theater-3000-returns-with-new-episodes-in-April/3151487781891/?spt=rrs&or=4|title='Mystery Science Theater 3000' returns with new episodes in April|newspaper=UPI|access-date=2017-02-22|language=en}}</ref> {{Aired episodes|2022|12|16|num=230|title=Mystery Science Theater 3000|released=y|finished=13}} A feature film, titled ''[[Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Movie]]'', was also released on April 19, 1996.

