=== Season 13 (2022)===
''[[Demon Squad]]'' and ''[[Robot Wars (film)|Robot Wars]]'' were announced early as the first two films to be featured in Season 13;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/movies/mst3k/mst3k-season-13-movies-revealed-kickstarter-make-more-mst3k|title=We Now Know the First Two Movies That Will be Featured on MST3K Season 13|website=Paste Magazine}}</ref> ''[[H. G. Wells' The Shape of Things to Come]]'', ''The Batwoman'', ''[[Santo en el tesoro de Drácula|Santo in the Treasure of Dracula]]'', ''[[Doctor Mordrid]]'', ''[[Gamera vs. Jiger]]'', ''[[Munchie]]'', ''[[The Bubble (1966 film)|The Bubble]]'', ''[[The Mask (1961 film)|The Mask 3D]]'', ''The Christmas Dragon'', ''[[Beyond Atlantis (film)|Beyond Atlantis]]'' and ''[[The Million Eyes of Sumuru]]'' were announced during the Turkey Day Marathon on November 25, 2021, ''Million Eyes'' having appeared over thirty years prior in the original KTMA season (albeit in an edited-for-content version) and is also featured as a video on demand from spiritual successor RiffTrax. Episodes are expected to roll out monthly throughout 2022, starting on March 4, culminating in ''The Christmas Dragon'' as a Christmas special and season finale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/mystery-science-theater-3000-season-13-movies/|title='Mystery Science Theater 3000' Unveils All 13 Movies for New Season|first=Shawnee|last=Haas|date=November 26, 2021|website=Collider}}</ref> ''Santo'', ''Robot Wars'', and ''Beyond Atlantis'' were shown in pre-release form as tests of the Gizmoplex to backers on the dates shown below, then were shown in their full form from May 6 to May 8, 2022.

